Strain Recipes
Mike's Bomba
Glentucky Family Farm · Sonoma · Energy: LOW
Grounded calm with clear mental edges.
Effects: Relaxed, Calm, Alert
Aroma: Fuel, Lemon Cream, Forest Floor
Dominant Terpene: β-Caryophyllene (0.47%)
Total Terpenes: 1.38%
Terpene Profile:

Terpene % Ratio
β-Caryophyllene 0.47 45%
Limonene 0.32 31%
α-Humulene 0.18 17%
Linalool 0.07 7%
Essential Oil Recipe: Black Pepper (20 drops), Lemon (10 drops), Sage (8 drops), Lavender (2
drops)
Black pepper delivers the dominant caryophyllene (50% of blend). Lemon matches
the lemon cream aroma. Sage provides humulene with herbal grounding. Lavender
softens edges.
Mocktail: Cream & Compass
Lemon-kissed calm with earthy rosemary anchors the mind.
Glass Coupe
Volume ~5 oz
Temp Ice cold
Ingredients:
● 2 oz Fresh lemon juice
● 1 oz Heavy cream
● 0.5 oz Rosemary-infused simple syrup
● 3 dashes Angostura bitters
● 1 twist Lemon peel
Method:
1. Add 2 oz fresh lemon juice, 1 oz cream, 0.5 oz rosemary-infused simple syrup to shaker
with ice.
2. Add 3 dashes of angostura bitters.
3. Shake for 10 seconds until frothy.
4. Fine-strain into chilled coupe.
5. Express lemon peel oil over surface and drop as garnish.

Terpene Map:
Terpene Source
β-Caryophyllene Rosemary infusion
Limonene Fresh lemon
α-Humulene Rosemary spice
Linalool Angostura bitters
Cocktail: Grounded Manhattan
Bourbon mellows the fuel, rosemary deepens the calm.
Glass Coupe
Volume ~5.5 oz
Temp Cold (around 45°F)
Style Classic/stirred
Spirit Bourbon (100 proof)
ABV ~35%
Ingredients:
● 2 oz Bourbon
● 1 oz Lemon cream cordial
● 0.5 oz Dry vermouth
● 0.5 oz Rosemary simple syrup
● 1 each Rosemary sprig & candied lemon
Method:
1. Combine 2 oz bourbon with 1 oz lemon cream cordial in mixing glass.
2. Add 0.5 oz dry vermouth and 0.5 oz rosemary syrup.
3. Stir for 15 seconds with large ice cubes.
4. Strain into chilled coupe.
5. Garnish with a rosemary sprig and candied lemon wheel.

Terpene Map:
Terpene Source
β-Caryophyllene Rosemary syrup
Limonene Lemon cordial
α-Humulene Rosemary +
vermouth
Linalool Vermouth botanicals
Juice / Smoothie: Forest Refresh
Pressed brightness with earthy mineral finish.
Glass Highball
Volume ~8 oz
Temp Ice cold
Format Cold-pressed blend
Timing Best within 2 hours of pressing
Ingredients:
● 3 oz Fresh lemon juice
● 2 oz Rosemary-steeped water
● 2 oz Coconut cream
● 1 oz Filtered water
● 1 each Fresh rosemary & lemon wheel
Method:
1. Cold-press 3 oz fresh lemon juice with 2 oz fresh rosemary water (steeped 20 min).
2. Strain through fine mesh.
3. Add 2 oz cold coconut cream and 1 oz filtered water.
4. Shake and pour over crushed ice.
5. Garnish with fresh rosemary sprig and lemon wheel.
Terpene Map:

Terpene Source
β-Caryophyllene Rosemary water
Limonene Fresh lemon
α-Humulene Rosemary notes
Linalool Coconut subtlety
Herbal Tea: Lemon & Sage Rest
Gentle herbal infusion with bright citrus notes.
Glass Teacup
Volume ~6 oz
Temp Warm (165-170°F when
served)
Steep
Temp
185°F
Steep Time 5 minutes
Caffeine 0 mg (herbal blend)
Ingredients:
● 6 oz Filtered water
● 1 tsp Dried rosemary
● 0.5 tsp Dried sage
● 1 wheel Dried lemon wheel
● 1 tsp Raw honey
Method:
1. Heat water to 185°F.
2. Add 1 tsp dried rosemary, 0.5 tsp dried sage, and 1 dried lemon wheel to infuser.
3. Steep for 5 minutes, stirring gently.
4. Remove infuser and add 0.5 oz fresh lemon juice and 1 tsp honey.
5. Stir and serve with a sage leaf.

