Guava Gift
Alpenglow Farms · Humboldt · Energy: HIGH
Open and expansive, easy social lift.
Effects: Social, Inspiring, Euphoric
Aroma: Fresh Guava, Lemon Rind, Tamarind
Dominant Terpene: β-Caryophyllene (0.73%)
Total Terpenes: 2.34%
Terpene Profile:
Terpene % Ratio
β-Caryophyllene 0.73 40%
Limonene 0.50 28%
Myrcene 0.33 18%
α-Humulene 0.25 14%
Essential Oil Recipe: Black Pepper (14 drops), Grapefruit (10 drops), Lemongrass (8 drops),
Basil (6 drops), Rosemary (2 drops)
Black pepper leads with caryophyllene. Grapefruit brings tropical citrus echoing the
guava aroma. Lemongrass delivers myrcene for euphoric lift.
Mocktail: Social Guava
Tropical guava and tamarind sparkle with expansive warmth.

Glass Highball
Volume ~8 oz
Temp Ice cold
Ingredients:
● 3 oz Fresh guava nectar
● 1 oz Tamarind paste (diluted)
● 3 oz Sparkling water
● 0.5 oz Fresh lemon juice
● 1 each Lemon wheel & rosemary sprig
Method:
1. Pour 3 oz fresh guava nectar into highball glass over ice.
2. Add 1 oz tamarind paste (dissolved in 1 oz water).
3. Top with 3 oz sparkling water.
4. Add 0.5 oz fresh lemon juice (juice, not zest).
5. Garnish with lemon wheel and rosemary sprig.
Terpene Map:
Terpene Source
β-Caryophyllene Tamarind + rosemary
Limonene Guava + lemon
Myrcene Guava fruit
α-Humulene Rosemary spice
Cocktail: Tropical Elevation
White rum carries guava and tamarind to bright social heights.
Glass Tiki mug
Volume ~7 oz

Temp Ice cold
Style Tropical/shaken
Spirit Pisco or white rum (40% ABV)
ABV ~28%
Ingredients:
● 2 oz Pisco or white rum
● 2.5 oz Guava puree
● 0.75 oz Tamarind paste
● 0.5 oz Lime juice
● 1 each Guava slice, lemon twist, rosemary
Method:
1. Combine 2 oz white rum (pisco preferred) with 2.5 oz guava puree in shaker.
2. Add 0.75 oz tamarind paste, 0.5 oz lime juice, and ice.
3. Shake vigorously for 12 seconds.
4. Strain into tiki mug filled with crushed ice.
5. Garnish with guava slice, lemon twist, and rosemary sprig.
Terpene Map:
Terpene Source
β-Caryophyllene Tamarind
Limonene Guava + lime
Myrcene Guava puree
α-Humulene Rosemary
accent
Juice / Smoothie: Guava Dawn
Pressed guava and tamarind with bright citrus whisper.
Glass Juice glass

Volume ~8 oz
Temp Ice cold
Format Cold-pressed fresh
Timing Consume within 1 hour for optimal brightness
Ingredients:
● 4 oz Fresh guava (pressed)
● 1 tsp Tamarind paste
● 1 oz Filtered water
● 0.5 oz Fresh lime juice
● 1 wheel Lemon wheel
Method:
1. Cold-press 4 oz fresh guava (with skin).
2. Strain through fine mesh into container.
3. Whisk in 1 tsp tamarind paste with 1 oz filtered water until smooth.
4. Add 0.5 oz fresh lime juice and combine.
5. Pour into glass over ice and garnish with lemon wheel.
