Essential Oil Recipe: Black Pepper (12 drops), Sweet Orange (10 drops), Rosemary (6 drops),
Sage (6 drops), Ylang Ylang (4 drops), Clove (2 drops)
The heaviest, most sedative strain. Black pepper and rosemary deliver
concentrated caryophyllene. Ylang ylang amplifies the blissful farnesene effect.
Mocktail: Velvet Descent
Coconut cream and nutmeg guide you into blissful surrender.
Glass Coupe
Volume ~5.5 oz
Temp Warm (145°F)
Ingredients:
● 2 oz Coconut cream (warmed)
● 0.25 tsp Freshly grated nutmeg
● 1 oz Vanilla oat milk
● 0.5 oz Fennel seed tea (cooled)
Method:

1. Heat 2 oz coconut cream gently (do not boil).
2. Toast 0.25 tsp freshly grated nutmeg in small pot for 10 seconds.
3. Whisk together coconut cream and nutmeg, remove from heat.
4. Add 1 oz vanilla oat milk and 0.5 oz fennel seed tea (steeped).
5. Pour into chilled coupe and float a small pinch of nutmeg on top.
