Juice / Smoothie: Peach Flambé Juice
White peach and cashew smoothness
Volume 8 oz
Temp chilled
Format fresh-pressed nut blend
Timing serve immediately to preserve peach
freshness
Ingredients:
● 2 ripe white peaches (peeled, pitted)
● 0.75 oz raw cashew butter
● 1 oz warm filtered water (for cashew milk)
● 0.5 oz fresh lemon juice
● 0.25 oz demerara syrup
● 1 oz cold filtered water
● peach slice (garnish)
● cinnamon dust (garnish)
● ice
Method:

1. Blend 2 ripe white peaches (peeled, pitted) until smooth (yields ~3 oz puree).
2. Strain through a fine mesh to remove any pulp.
3. Blend 0.75 oz raw cashew butter with 1 oz warm filtered water until milk-like.
4. Strain the cashew milk through cheesecloth.
5. Combine peach puree with cashew milk, 0.5 oz fresh lemon juice, and 0.25 oz demerara
syrup.
6. Stir in 1 oz cold filtered water to reach desired consistency.
7. Pour over ice in a tall glass and garnish with a peach slice and cinnamon dust.
