2. Brew 1 Earl Grey tea bag in 2 oz hot water for 3 minutes, then chill completely.
3. Blend 0.75 cup fresh green apple chunks until liquid (yields ~0.5 oz juice), strain through
cheesecloth.
4. Steep 4-5 dried chamomile flowers in 1 oz warm filtered water for 2 minutes, then chill.

5. Combine watermelon juice, cooled Earl Grey, apple juice, and chamomile water.
6. Add 0.5 oz fresh lemon juice and 0.5 oz chamomile-green apple syrup.
7. Add 1 oz cold filtered water to reach desired consistency.
8. Pour over ice and garnish with watermelon wedge and apple slice.
