Ingredients:
● 3-4 fresh mint leaves
● 0.75 oz white rum
● 0.75 oz fresh pineapple juice
● 0.25 oz fresh lime juice
● 0.1 oz ginger juice
● fresh mint leaf (garnish, on top)
● ice
Method:
1. Chill a shot glass in the freezer for 2 minutes.
2. In a mixing glass, muddle 3-4 fresh mint leaves very gently.
3. Add 0.75 oz white rum and 0.75 oz fresh pineapple juice.
4. Add 0.25 oz fresh lime juice and 0.1 oz ginger juice.
5. Stir with ice for 5 seconds.
6. Strain into the chilled shot glass and serve immediately with a mint leaf on top.
