Limonene lemon, pink grapefruit
Herbal Tea: Pink Rider Tea

Citrus and vanilla with gentle sparkling lift
Glass teacup
Volume 8 oz
Temp warm
Steep
Temp
185°F (85°C)
Steep Time 4 minutes
Caffeine none (herbal
blend)
Ingredients:
● 8 oz filtered water
● 1 tsp dried pink grapefruit peel
● 0.75 tsp dried lemon peel
● 3-4 dried green apple pieces
● 0.5 tsp dried basil
● 0.25 tsp dried rosemary
● tiny pinch of vanilla powder
● 0.25 oz sugar syrup or honey
● 0.1 oz vanilla extract
● thin pink grapefruit wheel (garnish)
● lemon peel (garnish)
Method:
1. Heat 8 oz filtered water to 185°F (85°C).
2. In a tea infuser, combine 1 tsp dried pink grapefruit peel, 0.75 tsp dried lemon peel, 3-4
dried green apple pieces, 0.5 tsp dried basil, 0.25 tsp dried rosemary, and a tiny pinch of
vanilla powder.
3. Steep for 4 minutes to extract the bright citrus character.
4. Strain into a warm teacup.
5. Stir in 0.25 oz sugar syrup or honey and 0.1 oz vanilla extract.
6. Garnish with a thin pink grapefruit wheel and lemon peel.
